# Step 7: Helm Charts — Build Log & Decisions

## What Step 7 Delivered

One reusable Helm chart that deploys all four Bebeque Energy
microservices to EKS. Validated locally with helm lint and
helm template. Deployed live to staging and confirmed running.

---

## The Core Design Decision — One Chart, Not Four

The first decision in Step 7 was the chart architecture.

Two options existed:
- Four separate charts, one per service
- One base chart with per-service values files

We chose one base chart. The reason is the golden path principle.
When a fifth service is onboarded, a developer creates one new
values file — not an entire chart. When a bug is fixed in
deployment.yaml it is fixed once, not four times. Four separate
charts drift over time and become inconsistent. One chart with
values files is the platform team pattern.

